radiographic_examinations.findings: Elevated levels of aspartate aminotransferase (960 U/liter) and alanine aminotransferase (347 U/liter); previous liver function tests 2 months prior were normal (19 U/liter)
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Within 5 days of discontinuing lamotrigine, aspartate aminotransferase levels returned to the normal range; alanine aminotransferase levels remained mildly elevated at 102 U/liter
